There here and they came for one thing rabits. This is what the
 government tried to hide

New Sounds, Alien butterflies and flies,
Where did gravity go?

 I Done This Level Whith All Logos I'v Found On The Games They Have !

This is my first level, hope you like it. There's a lot of nothingness =
in it, it's good for more than two players.

This map is my first map and i have tested it a fair bit.
It has been tested with 3 players and we played for 3 hours straight
 (thats how addictive this game is).

description: Another lovely little level those those dudes to slode about on, again this one is for my woman, Heather and it plays better than the last one me thinkuth, let me know if ya agree.

author: Proto Bailey
description: Yes thats right those little bunnies are in a cool place, this one is for my beloved, Heather who loves seeing them sliding about.

My first level, made with paint... lots of fun... more 
addictive than cocaine...

description: I made this level through pencil drawing and then scanned it in.

I just took my old level and cut and pasted onto Crystal2.
 With this level there is a lot more action towards the top.

 The design centers around the tower in the middle of the map.

water, slippery slime etc.?) After you play this, you'll beg for more.

 the level is more based on design than looks

cosmic butterflies.

This is my first level.
I used MGI Photosuite to make the graphics.
Hope u like it!

Includes photo realistic graphics and lots

Their killer zombie bunny rabbits and there out for proto-blood! Didn't

The way to play this is to play it like King of The Castle

and you'll appear.

Features: My Desktop

I only modified the included

This level is great for playing if you like constant action and is  
great for 3 or 4 player games.

It looks very similar to the original mario bros. on Nintendo, and
 has lots of room to move as well as lots of different places go.

Part the Red Sea with your own two paws
Follow the prophet Mijji as he rids you 
of this world.  DIE!

 it more colorful and implemented transparent water (kinda of...).

This level contains only water and ice and so forces you
to keep moving nearly all the time.

I used Adobe Photoshop to make the graphics on the level
Have fun!

Well after much complaining and whining...I figured out how to
make a level. Why it's called Point Zero? Because it's just a level to test out how to do it.  The next one will be better.. I promise.

This is a freaky level. Enjoy randomly disapeering into the

Down, down to Rabbit Town...
Have fun!

Hey.. There should be a level just like that first screen of j&b;!
So i did one...

There are a couple of places where a single rabbit can get stuck, but
two rabbits working with/against each other can get out.

TThis is an extremely simple level, meant for a RUMBLE gameplay.
No strategy, nowhere to run, nowhere to hide,just outsmarting your opponents.
Best played with 3 players, never tried with 4.

I've learned from the mistakes I made in the first one.
There's a lot of air in this one and nicer graphics.

This is my first real level which has a cool waterfall!
